Configuring RStudio and GitHub
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Next, we need to configure Rstudio to use Roxogyn2 to generate documentation
 files.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
To Configure: Build>Configure Build Tools>Build Tools>Check 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Generate documentation with Roxygen
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

> Check all boxes>OK.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Next, Go to Tools>Global Options>Git/SVN and create RSA key.
 Enter a password you can remember.
 After that, click View public key and copy it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Go to GitHub.
 Go into Edit Profile on your main page.
 Select SSH Keys.
 Add SSH Key.
 Title it and paste the RSA key that you copied into the key field on github.
 Click 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Add Key
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Separator

\end_layout

\begin_layout Frame
\begin_inset Argument 4
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
More GitHub Configuration
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
Now to connect our new package with a GitHub repository.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
First make sure that the repository is created.
 You do this on GitHub.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Next, we will connect GitHub and our project.
 In RStudio, Select Git by the Environment window.
 Select More, then Shell.
 Type the following commands:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
git remote add origin git@github.com:githubusername/repositoryname.git
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
git push -u origin master (be sure to commit changes before trying to push)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
Only remove origin, githubusername, and repositoryname with your a name
 of the repository, specific github username ,and the specific repository
 name.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\end_deeper
\end_deeper
